gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: A
task: A3
title: "UX: loading.tsx skeletons for PDP + equipment segments — absorb 15s hono timeout (#1257)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P1
refs:
  - CROP-front#1257
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, REACT_SERVER_COMPONENTS, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  PDP and equipment segments show a blank screen for up to 15s when hono times out.
  Next.js loading.tsx files provide instant skeleton UI while the segment resolves.
  Add loading.tsx to PDP (app/parts/[id]/) and equipment (app/equipment/[slug]/)
  segments so users see a meaningful skeleton within ~200ms instead of a blank page.

scope:
  in:
    - app/parts/[id]/loading.tsx — PDP skeleton (image placeholder, title bar, price bar, tabs)
    - app/equipment/[slug]/loading.tsx — equipment skeleton (header, parts-diagrams section)
    - Skeletons use Moby DS tokens and Tailwind animate-pulse
    - Visual smoke: localhost at throttled network → skeleton appears immediately
  out:
    - Changing actual page components or data fetching
    - Error boundaries (separate concern)
    - Any other segments beyond PDP + equipment

invariants:
  - No hardcoded hex colors — Moby DS tokens only
  - No React.memo / unjustified useMemo/useCallback
  - Skeleton must not flicker on fast loads (acceptable: briefly visible then replaced)

acceptance:
  - Throttled network: PDP skeleton visible within 200ms, replaced by real content on load
  - Equipment skeleton same
  - Desktop + mobile viewports look reasonable (no layout shift beyond CLS budget)

dep: A2   # A2 tags the timeout in Sentry; A3 fixes the UX symptom — logical order
output: app/parts/[id]/loading.tsx + app/equipment/[slug]/loading.tsx
